place.name: KINGSTON
place.gazetteerText: KINGSTONE, a parish in Bridge district, Kent; on an affluent of the river Stour, 2½ miles S of Beaksbourne r. station, and 5 SE of Canterbury. Post town, Canterbury. Acres, 1, 525. Real property, £2, 227. Pop., 273. Houses, 57. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Canterbury. Value, £500. * Patron, Sir J. W. E. Bridges, Bart. The church is good.. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
